<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='175928' id='t-175928'>so big numbers, really big numbers.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='178598' id='t-178598'>And we calculated several scenarios,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='180711' id='t-180711'>and the picture always looked like this.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 3:15
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='184565' id='t-184565'>Now, to close the gap,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='186446' id='t-186446'>Germany has to significantly
increase migration,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='190509' id='t-190509'>get many more women in the workforce,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='192715' id='t-192715'>increase retirement age —</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='194480' id='t-194480'>by the way, we just
lowered it this year —</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='196895' id='t-196895'>and all these measures at once.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='199658' id='t-199658'>If Germany fails here,
Germany will stagnate.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='203721' id='t-203721'>We won't grow anymore. Why?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='206043' id='t-206043'>Because the workers are not there
who can generate this growth.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='209456' id='t-209456'>And companies will look
for talents somewhere else.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='213913' id='t-213913'>But where?</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 3:47
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='216730' id='t-216730'>Now, we simulated labor supply
and labor demand</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='220776' id='t-220776'>for the largest 15 economies in the world,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='223945' id='t-223945'>representing more than 70 percent
