<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='227637' id='t-227637'>and the overall picture
looks like this by 2020.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='231584' id='t-231584'>Blue indicates a labor surplus,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='234277' id='t-234277'>red indicates a labor shortfall,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='236762' id='t-236762'>and gray are those countries
which are borderline.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='240454' id='t-240454'>So by 2020, we still see a labor surplus
in some countries,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='246560' id='t-246560'>like Italy, France, the U.S.,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='248743' id='t-248743'>but this picture will change
